{{/*
  All user-facing terminal copy lives here, as named text/template blocks.
  Rendered against a *view* (see config.go): installation fields come from the
  embedded *Config (.UserHost, .SSHUser, .SSHHost, .AppDomain, .ShortLen),
  per-session values are the view's own fields (.PubKey, .Bolt11, .ShortName,
  .QRW/.QRH/.W/.H). Whitespace inside each define is significant — it is what
  the client sees. "upper" is the only custom func.
*/}}

{{define "banner"}}
Welcome to {{.UserHost}}. Make your local http application available
on a subdomain https://<YOUR>.{{.AppDomain}}.

<YOUR> stands for a random {{.ShortLen}}-letter shortname that you receive
after paying a Bitcoin Lightning invoice. Payment is required once for
each SSH key you use for logging in. As long as you use the same key
again, your subdomain name will be always yours, for the lifetime of
this project.

If you're running a web application locally on http://localhost:5000,
forwarding it to your subdomain is done like this:

  ssh -R80:localhost:5000 {{.UserHost}}

Port 80 ^ here is just a convention, as you're forwarding your
unencrypted server to the remote machine. Our reverse proxy handles
HTTPS for your subdomain.

{{end}}

{{define "greeting"}}{{upper .UserHost}} knows you...

Authorizing key: {{.PubKey}}
{{end}}

{{/* STABILITY CONTRACT: the "Please pay: <bolt11>" and "Your forwarded site:
   <url>" lines are parsed by scripts and agents (grep/awk) and documented in
   SKILL.md. Keep these exact prefixes intact. */}}
{{define "pleasePay"}}Please pay: {{.Bolt11}}
{{end}}

{{define "qrTooLarge"}}
QR code ({{.QRW}}x{{.QRH}}) too large for the screen ({{.W}}x{{.H}})
Relogin with larger window / smaller font to get it.

{{end}}

{{define "site"}}Your forwarded site: https://{{.ShortName}}.{{.AppDomain}}
{{end}}

{{define "forwarding"}}Connections are forwarded until you exit.
{{end}}

{{define "hint"}}Hint: use ssh -R80:localhost:5000 {{.UserHost}}
if you have your application listening on port 5000
{{end}}

